               <p>ALEXANDER SMYTH. I live in Mark-lane. On the 14th of January I was coming from Covent-garden Theatre; I walked as far as <placeName id="t18290115-257-crimeloc1386">Norfolk-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290115-257-crimeloc1386" type="placeName" value="Norfolk-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290115-257-crimeloc1386" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-257-off1384 t18290115-257-crimeloc1386"></join> - Mrs. Smyth had hold of my arm, and I had my umbrella in my right hand; I felt a severe pull at it, but I did not let it go: presently I felt a more severe pull, which bent my wrist, opened my hand, and got away my umbrella; I pursued the prisoner - a gentleman followed, and took him: I came up, and he was delivered up to me - I gave him in charge; I am certain he is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-257-person1949">
                  WILLIAM 
                  JOHN McBEATH
               <interp inst="t18290115-257-person1949" type="surname" value="JOHN McBEATH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-257-person1949" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-257-person1949" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was on my way from Waterloo-bridge to Norfolk - street; I saw this gentleman and his lady followed by the prisoner - I saw the Strand; which got the umbrella from him; the gentleman called out that he had robbed him of his umbrella: I followed the prisoner, and took him by the New church in the Strand; I am positive he is the man.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
